.SH NAME
parent_allows_removal \- verify if it's ok to remove an exception
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" parent_allows_removal
.BI "(struct dev_cgroup *childcg "  ","
.BI "struct dev_exception_item *ex "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "childcg" 12
child cgroup from where the exception will be removed
.IP "ex" 12
exception being removed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When removing an exception in cgroups with default ALLOW policy, it must
be checked if removing it will give the child cgroup more access than the
parent.
.SH "RETURN"
true if it's ok to remove exception, false otherwise
